âœ… Task 1: Install and Configure Git
1. Verify Git is installed
git --version


Expected output (example):

git version 2.43.0

2. Set your Git identity
git config --global user.name "Akash Nimje"
git config --global user.email "akash@example.com"


(Use your real email)

3. Verify configuration
git config --list


You should see:

user.name=Akash Nimje
user.email=akash@example.com



âœ… Task 2: Create Your Git Project
